Creating and disposing of memory chunks
---------------------------------------

   Memory to be used solely by the user C code can be
reserved/disposed of using, e.g., the well-known `malloc()'/`free()'
functions (or whatever other functions the user may have available).
However, memory explicitly allocated by Ciao Prolog and passed to C
code, or allocated by C code and passed on to Ciao Prolog (and
subject to garbage collection by it) should be allotted and freed
(when necessary) by using the functions:

   * `void *ciao_malloc(int size);'

   * `void ciao_free(void *pointer);'


whose behavior is similar to `malloc()'/`free()', but which will
cooordinate properly with Ciao Prolog's internal memory management.


